WEBVTT

00:03.536 --> 00:05.572
[***]

00:09.442 --> 00:11.111
[SNORING]

00:11.144 --> 00:13.580
[WHISPERING]
Chris.

00:13.613 --> 00:15.548
Chris.

00:15.582 --> 00:18.418
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>Because I had to catch the bus</i>

00:18.451 --> 00:21.187
<i>to go all the way across town</i>
<i>to get to school,</i>

00:21.221 --> 00:23.390
<i>I got 10 hours</i>
<i>less sleep a week</i>

00:23.423 --> 00:26.559
<i>than anyone else in my class.</i>

00:26.593 --> 00:27.660
[BELL RINGS]

00:27.694 --> 00:29.696
<i>One time,</i>
<i>I fell asleep so long,</i>

00:29.729 --> 00:31.464
<i>I woke up with a mustache.</i>

00:33.433 --> 00:35.735
Did I miss anything?
Not this time.

00:35.769 --> 00:39.539
You gotta watch it. You were
this close to getting caught.

00:41.474 --> 00:44.110
Well, at least it's Friday.

00:44.144 --> 00:45.712
I'll get a chance
to sleep in tomorrow.

00:45.745 --> 00:47.847
<i>Man, there was nothing</i>
<i>like being in bed</i>

00:47.881 --> 00:51.451
<i>on a Saturday morning,</i>
<i>dreaming my favorite dream:</i>

00:51.484 --> 00:54.354
<i>me sleeping in</i>
<i>on a Saturday morning.</i>

00:55.588 --> 00:57.323
You gonna watch<i>Rocky</i>tomorrow?

00:57.357 --> 00:59.693
<i>My favorite movie</i>
<i>of all time was</i>Rocky.

00:59.726 --> 01:02.362
<i>A black man</i>
<i>kicking a white guy's ass.</i>

01:02.395 --> 01:05.632
<i>My father thought the movie</i>
<i>should've been called</i>Apollo.

01:05.665 --> 01:07.200
Oh, I can't.

01:07.233 --> 01:10.503
My TV's out.
No TV all weekend?

01:11.805 --> 01:13.606
Are you gonna be okay?

01:13.640 --> 01:15.241
Yeah.

01:15.275 --> 01:18.745
So, what are you gonna do?
I'm going to sleep.

01:18.778 --> 01:21.281
<i>I was so sleepy,</i>
<i>instead of counting sheep,</i>

01:21.314 --> 01:23.583
<i>I was counting sleep.</i>

01:23.616 --> 01:26.152
[***]

01:31.491 --> 01:34.394
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>

01:59.686 --> 02:02.889
<i>The only person who loved sleep</i>
<i>more than me was my father.</i>

02:02.922 --> 02:05.859
<i>And right now, he's dreaming</i>
his<i>favorite dream.</i>

02:05.892 --> 02:07.527
I've been working here
a long time.

02:07.560 --> 02:09.462
I've never seen anybody
pay bills like you.

02:09.496 --> 02:11.431
You got two jobs or something?
Just one.

02:11.464 --> 02:13.233
Can I help you
with something else?

02:13.266 --> 02:14.968
Can I have my
three cents change?

02:15.001 --> 02:16.603
ROCHELLE:
Julius.

02:16.636 --> 02:18.271
Julius.

02:20.407 --> 02:22.876
Julius!
Yo, I'm up, I'm up, I'm up.

02:22.909 --> 02:24.444
Where are my keys?
No, no, baby!

02:24.477 --> 02:26.246
You don't have to go to work.

02:26.279 --> 02:27.514
Today is Saturday.

02:27.547 --> 02:29.516
You woke me up at 6:45
on a Saturday morning?

02:29.549 --> 02:31.217
Are you crazy?
No, look, wait.

02:31.251 --> 02:32.585
I was looking through the paper

02:32.619 --> 02:34.854
and they're having
TVs on sale in Queens.

02:34.888 --> 02:37.857
Look, 199 for a color 19-inch?!

02:37.891 --> 02:39.726
<i>Nineteen-inch TV? Hey!</i>

02:39.759 --> 02:41.661
<i>Now guys have those</i>
<i>in their headrests,</i>

02:41.695 --> 02:44.264
<i>but back then,</i>
<i>it was a big deal.</i>

02:44.297 --> 02:47.634
Rochelle, I can get
this same TV for half that.

02:47.667 --> 02:49.703
All I gotta do is wait
for my man Risky to get one.

02:49.736 --> 02:52.672
<i>That means he has to wait for</i>
<i>his man Risky to steal one.</i>

02:52.706 --> 02:54.841
Oh, no, no, no,
I am tired of Risky.

02:54.874 --> 02:58.411
Everything we get
from him breaks down.

02:58.445 --> 03:00.947
What are you doing?
I'm ironing.

03:00.980 --> 03:03.616
I got you an iron from Risky.
It broke.

03:03.650 --> 03:05.985
Damn, Risky.

03:06.019 --> 03:08.488
What are you doing?
I'm making toast.

03:08.521 --> 03:11.658
I got you a toaster from Risky.
It broke!

03:11.691 --> 03:12.959
Damn, Risky.

03:12.992 --> 03:14.427
Are you sure?
Like I told you

03:14.461 --> 03:16.296
for the hundredth time,
I'm pregnant.

03:16.329 --> 03:18.264
I thought you used a condom.
I did.

03:18.298 --> 03:19.466
Damn Risky.

03:21.334 --> 03:23.970
What are you doing now?

03:24.004 --> 03:27.273
I'm reading the small print.
Yeah.

03:27.307 --> 03:30.977
199 for a 19-inch TV.
Uh-huh.

03:31.011 --> 03:34.381
Must be a catch.

03:34.414 --> 03:36.483
No! The catch is
if they run out,

03:36.516 --> 03:40.954
we won't be getting one.
Now, get up!

03:40.987 --> 03:42.989
ROCHELLE:
Chris!

03:43.023 --> 03:45.425
Chris!
Huh?! What?

03:45.458 --> 03:47.627
Get up. I need you to go
to the laundromat.

03:47.660 --> 03:49.929
I don't want to go.
I'm tired.

03:49.963 --> 03:53.466
Me and your father are going
to buy a new TV today.

03:53.500 --> 03:56.803
So I need you to do this!

03:56.836 --> 03:58.538
Come on, if you do this,

03:58.571 --> 04:00.440
I'll let you
watch<i>Rocky</i>tonight.

04:00.473 --> 04:02.909
So, please, do not mix
the colors and the whites.

04:02.942 --> 04:05.779
And those dryers get real hot,
so set it to medium

04:05.812 --> 04:07.781
so you won't
shrink anything, okay?

04:07.814 --> 04:09.816
<i>I didn't hear a word after,</i>
<i>"Get up."</i>

04:09.849 --> 04:13.520
I can't take all that by myself.
Drew and Tonya are going.

04:13.553 --> 04:16.423
Do I have to take Tonya?
You need help, don't you?!

04:16.456 --> 04:17.957
Now, hurry up!

04:17.991 --> 04:20.760
It's Saturday morning.
All the machines will be taken.

04:20.794 --> 04:22.996
I know you don't want to be
there all day.

04:23.029 --> 04:25.065
Just everybody get up.

04:25.098 --> 04:26.633
<i>There are three places</i>

04:26.666 --> 04:28.635
<i>a kid doesn't wanna be</i>
<i>on the weekend:</i>

04:28.668 --> 04:33.840
<i>at a funeral...</i>
[SOBBING] Why? Oh, why?

04:33.873 --> 04:37.777
<i>...at a woman's</i>
<i>department store...</i>

04:37.811 --> 04:41.648
<i>and at a laundromat</i>
<i>on a Saturday morning.</i>

04:41.681 --> 04:44.584
<i>A laundromat is a place</i>
<i>where really poor people go</i>

04:44.617 --> 04:46.419
<i>to wash their clothes.</i>

04:46.453 --> 04:48.355
You don't want that one,
that's broke.

04:48.388 --> 04:51.057
Use the other, use that one.

04:51.091 --> 04:52.559
I was gonna use this one.

04:52.592 --> 04:54.594
You better get out of
my face, little boy.

04:54.627 --> 04:56.629
<i>At the laundromat,</i>
<i>even a nice woman</i>

04:56.663 --> 04:59.833
<i>would smack her mother twice</i>
<i>for an empty machine.</i>

04:59.866 --> 05:02.635
Okay, y'all go check
those machines

05:02.669 --> 05:04.804
and see what cycles they're on.

05:04.838 --> 05:06.973
I don't wanna check it,
you check it.

05:07.007 --> 05:08.508
Well, then go sit down.

05:08.541 --> 05:10.710
I don't wanna sit down.
Well, then stand up.

05:10.744 --> 05:12.412
<i>It took me years to realize</i>

05:12.445 --> 05:13.880
<i>if you want a girl</i>
<i>to do something,</i>

05:13.913 --> 05:15.882
<i>you gotta tell her</i>
<i>to do the opposite.</i>

05:15.915 --> 05:18.985
Here's your chicken.
You better not bring me dessert.

05:19.019 --> 05:20.687
I'll get you
what I wanna get you!

05:20.720 --> 05:23.423
<i>Only one place that didn't</i>
<i>work: the bedroom.</i>

05:23.456 --> 05:26.426
Okay, this one's on spin.

05:26.459 --> 05:28.061
And this one's on wash.

05:28.094 --> 05:30.130
Good, now, I need you
to watch them.

05:31.931 --> 05:33.133
Can I get the quarters?

05:33.166 --> 05:34.701
No. I don't want you
to lose them.

05:34.734 --> 05:36.469
Ain't nobody
gonna lose nothing.

05:36.503 --> 05:38.905
It's just right there.

05:38.938 --> 05:41.875
<i>She looked at me</i>
<i>like I stole her cocoa.</i>

05:41.908 --> 05:43.143
Fine.

05:43.176 --> 05:45.612
<i>I would've let her</i>
<i>smack me silly</i>

05:45.645 --> 05:48.415
<i>if it would have made her</i>
<i>act right.</i>

05:52.185 --> 05:55.588
Rocky, here I come.

05:55.622 --> 05:57.624
You into martial arts?

05:58.892 --> 06:00.994
Yeah. Why?

06:01.027 --> 06:04.764
Want to learn some kill moves?
Yeah.

06:04.798 --> 06:06.766
<i>The only thing Drew loved</i>
<i>more than candy</i>

06:06.800 --> 06:08.835
<i>was learning</i>
<i>how to break a neck.</i>

06:08.868 --> 06:11.438
Right there under the guy's
nose, you just take it...

06:11.471 --> 06:13.173
Boom!

06:15.909 --> 06:18.044
[MUTTERING SOFTLY]

06:18.078 --> 06:19.746
[QUARTERS TINKLING ON FLOOR]

06:19.779 --> 06:21.848
Tonya, what'd I tell you?!

06:23.550 --> 06:25.051
Well, you could at least help.

06:25.085 --> 06:28.988
I would if you'd stop hollering.
You're the one who dropped them!

06:36.162 --> 06:37.764
[SIGHS]

06:41.701 --> 06:43.636
Wake me up
when that machine stops.

06:43.670 --> 06:45.472
I ain't waking you up.

06:45.505 --> 06:47.173
Tonya, I'm not playing with you.

06:47.207 --> 06:49.209
Now, wake me up
when that machine stops!

06:49.242 --> 06:52.112
<i>Tonya's so difficult,</i>
<i>the only reason she's a girl</i>

06:52.145 --> 06:55.915
<i>is 'cause my father</i>
<i>wanted a boy.</i>

06:55.949 --> 06:57.684
Oh, that's nice. Oh!

06:57.717 --> 06:59.185
Okay, let me tell you the rules.

06:59.219 --> 07:00.754
Okay.
We're gonna get a TV.

07:00.787 --> 07:01.955
Mm-hm.
Not a VCR.

07:01.988 --> 07:03.923
I hear you. I got you.
Not a couch.

07:03.957 --> 07:05.225
A TV.
No problem.

07:05.258 --> 07:07.927
And if it doesn't cost 199,
we're going home.

07:07.961 --> 07:08.895
<i>Yeah, right.</i>

07:08.928 --> 07:10.864
Well, can I at least
look around?

07:10.897 --> 07:12.866
Last time you went
"looking around,"

07:12.899 --> 07:14.934
I ended up buying a house.
Can I help you?

07:14.968 --> 07:18.672
Yeah, we're here for the 199
19-inch color TV.

07:18.705 --> 07:20.273
I'm sorry, we sold out of those.

07:20.306 --> 07:23.810
Sale's been going since Monday.
Thank you. Okay, let's go.

07:23.843 --> 07:26.079
I'm sure we can find
something else you might like.

07:26.112 --> 07:27.814
See?
You probably can,

07:27.847 --> 07:31.084
but if it's not a TV for 199,
you don't need to show it to me.

07:31.117 --> 07:32.585
No, no, no, wait, baby.

07:32.619 --> 07:34.120
Now, let's just...

07:34.154 --> 07:37.090
look around for a little while.
You got "looking around" money?

07:37.123 --> 07:40.226
Sir, I don't mean to intrude,
but you a union man?

07:40.260 --> 07:43.697
Um, yeah,
I'm in the local. Why?

07:43.730 --> 07:45.999
Says right here,
show me a union card,

07:46.032 --> 07:48.068
you get credit on the spot.
Say what?!

07:48.101 --> 07:50.270
<i>Let's just say my mother</i>
<i>didn't have</i>

07:50.303 --> 07:52.872
<i>the best history with credit.</i>

07:54.074 --> 07:56.009
Put it on the card.
<i>She bought shoes,</i>

07:56.042 --> 07:58.645
<i>she bought clothes, she'd</i>
<i>buy money, if they let her.</i>

07:58.678 --> 08:00.246
Put it on the card.

08:00.280 --> 08:03.083
<i>There was nothing my mother</i>
<i>wouldn't put on a credit card.</i>

08:03.116 --> 08:05.585
Put this on my card.
Lady, you can't pay

08:05.618 --> 08:08.188
your credit card bill
with your credit card.

08:08.221 --> 08:09.856
What about this one?

08:09.889 --> 08:12.759
We came here to get a $199 TV,
not a credit card.

08:12.792 --> 08:14.227
But you could use one, right?

08:14.260 --> 08:15.695
We'll give you a $500 limit,

08:15.729 --> 08:16.963
no payments for six months.

08:16.996 --> 08:18.832
We'll get you out of here
with a TV.

08:18.865 --> 08:20.133
Come on.
Wait, wait, baby.

08:20.166 --> 08:22.802
Let's think about this
for a moment.

08:22.836 --> 08:24.604
If the kids
keep watching that TV,

08:24.637 --> 08:25.872
they'll mess up their eyes,

08:25.905 --> 08:27.841
and if they can't see,
they might wander

08:27.874 --> 08:29.743
into the street
and get hit by a bus.

08:29.776 --> 08:32.779
Now, do you want three
crippled kids or a new TV?

08:32.812 --> 08:34.114
Lady's got a point.
See?

08:34.147 --> 08:38.251
Would you please?
This is...nice!

08:38.284 --> 08:40.887
<i>Instead of watching</i>
<i>the machines like I told him,</i>

08:40.920 --> 08:43.757
<i>Drew was perfecting</i>
<i>the Flying Monkey Death Claw.</i>

08:43.790 --> 08:46.659
One more time, one more time,
one more time.

08:46.693 --> 08:49.229
Aah! Man, what are you doing?!

08:49.262 --> 08:51.598
<i>Damn, black Yoda.</i>

08:51.631 --> 08:53.066
Uh-uh...

08:53.099 --> 08:54.634
Uh-uh.

08:54.668 --> 08:55.935
Oh!

08:57.671 --> 08:59.172
How come you didn't wake me up?

08:59.205 --> 09:01.841
You don't tell me what to do.
Where'd you get that?

09:01.875 --> 09:05.078
That machine.
You spent our quarters?

09:05.111 --> 09:07.981
I was thirsty.
Oh, man, we need those!

09:08.014 --> 09:10.784
We won't even have enough
for the dryers!

09:10.817 --> 09:12.118
So?

09:15.055 --> 09:17.691
What happened to our clothes?
I don't know.

09:17.724 --> 09:19.325
Drew, who took our clothes?

09:19.359 --> 09:21.795
Wasn't me.

09:21.828 --> 09:24.097
Somebody stole our clothes.

09:24.130 --> 09:26.232
It's not my fault.

09:26.266 --> 09:28.668
Yes, it is.
Instead of going to get a soda,

09:28.702 --> 09:30.737
how come you
weren't watching the clothes?

09:30.770 --> 09:32.005
How come<i>you</i>weren't
watching them?

09:32.038 --> 09:34.641
I was asleep!
I told you to wake me up!

09:34.674 --> 09:37.744
You're always messing stuff up.
I hate you!

09:39.279 --> 09:41.114
I don't care.

09:44.184 --> 09:46.319
Where you going?
None of your business,

09:46.353 --> 09:49.322
that's where I'm going.

09:49.356 --> 09:53.827
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

10:01.768 --> 10:04.371
Hey, little man.
Everything all right?

10:04.404 --> 10:05.972
I lost my clothes.

10:06.006 --> 10:08.341
What you mean,
you lost your clothes?

10:08.375 --> 10:09.909
They were in two baskets.

10:09.943 --> 10:12.012
I was waiting for the machine
and fell asleep.

10:12.045 --> 10:14.214
What they look like?
Um, I don't know,

10:14.247 --> 10:15.348
there's lots of stuff.

10:15.382 --> 10:17.183
Pants, underwear, socks.

10:17.217 --> 10:19.786
Uh-huh. Is that them over there?

10:19.819 --> 10:21.821
Yeah! Thanks.
Yeah, right, uh-huh.

10:21.855 --> 10:23.690
Go ahead with your bad self.

10:27.761 --> 10:29.095
[MACHINE BUZZES]

10:29.129 --> 10:31.865
<i>At the laundromat,</i>
<i>empty washing machines</i>

10:31.898 --> 10:34.367
<i>come around less</i>
<i>than a Sade tour.</i>

10:34.401 --> 10:36.936
[***]

10:41.074 --> 10:45.311
<i>Terrell Owens ain't got</i>
<i>nothin' on her.</i>

10:45.345 --> 10:47.914
I'm using this one.

10:47.947 --> 10:51.751
Oh! Little dude
from across the street.

10:51.785 --> 10:54.087
Why don't you let me
hold a quarter?

11:05.432 --> 11:08.368
Didn't mama say not to mix
the coloreds with the whites?

11:08.401 --> 11:13.273
I only have enough quarters
for one machine and the dryers.

11:13.306 --> 11:15.041
[GRUNTS]

11:15.075 --> 11:18.945
Finish this
and watch the clothes.

11:18.978 --> 11:21.815
I'm gonna go find Tonya.

11:25.118 --> 11:28.221
All you got to do is sign on the
dotted line and we're all set.

11:28.254 --> 11:30.924
I'm reading the small print.
It don't mean nothing.

11:30.957 --> 11:34.761
Then why'd they put it on here?
It's just technicalities.

11:34.794 --> 11:36.396
Seventeen percent?

11:36.429 --> 11:39.366
That's kind of high, ain't it?
It's not unusual.

11:39.399 --> 11:42.168
Brooklyn Bridge ain't unusual,
but it's still high.

11:42.202 --> 11:43.970
<i>You should've seen him</i>
<i>at tax time.</i>

11:44.004 --> 11:46.306
Done yet, baby?
I want to show you something.

11:46.339 --> 11:47.941
I'm reading the contract.

11:47.974 --> 11:50.377
Oh, just hurry up and sign
that thing and come on.

11:50.410 --> 11:52.045
I want to show you this couch.

11:52.078 --> 11:53.980
<i>The only thing that made</i>
<i>my mother happier</i>

11:54.014 --> 11:57.917
<i> than having a man with two job</i>
<i>was getting a new couch.</i>

11:59.953 --> 12:03.490
Girl, did I tell you
I was getting married?

12:03.523 --> 12:06.793
Ooh, that is nice.

12:06.826 --> 12:08.261
But did I show you
my new couch?

12:08.294 --> 12:10.130
<i>No amount of good news</i>
<i>could compare</i>

12:10.163 --> 12:12.198
<i>to my mother</i>
<i>getting a new couch.</i>

12:12.232 --> 12:14.067
It's all leather.

12:14.100 --> 12:16.136
[CHUCKLES]

12:16.169 --> 12:19.372
Hey, listen, you sign it now,
I'm gonna give you a $700 limit.

12:19.406 --> 12:21.341
Seven--

12:21.374 --> 12:23.276
Seven hundred dollars?

12:23.309 --> 12:27.814
Julius, do you know
what I could do with $700?!

12:27.847 --> 12:29.849
<i>Unfortunately, he does.</i>
Thank you!

12:29.883 --> 12:31.951
Rochelle, do you know how long

12:31.985 --> 12:34.454
it's gonna take me
to pay off $700?

12:34.487 --> 12:36.289
Hm?

12:36.322 --> 12:38.191
Oh, but Julius...

12:38.224 --> 12:41.094
<i>If the most important thing to</i>
<i>my mother was buying a couch,</i>

12:41.127 --> 12:44.097
<i>the most important thing</i>
<i>to my father was paying it off.</i>

12:44.130 --> 12:46.866
Oh, Julius, where have you been?

12:46.900 --> 12:48.368
I just dropped Tonya off
at college.

12:48.401 --> 12:50.570
They hired Chris to replace me
on my first job,

12:50.603 --> 12:52.405
and Drew to replace me
on my second job.

12:52.439 --> 12:55.108
I paid off the house, car,
light bill and the gas.

12:55.141 --> 12:57.077
We don't owe anybody
a single dime.

12:57.110 --> 12:59.512
I'm gonna take a nap
and get the hell out of here

12:59.546 --> 13:01.614
before you spend
some more money.

13:01.648 --> 13:03.249
This is a good deal.

13:03.283 --> 13:06.619
See, baby, we could get
a lot of stuff we need.

13:06.653 --> 13:09.255
I mean, it's on credit.
What are you worried about?

13:09.289 --> 13:11.991
It's on credit.
That's what I'm worried about.

13:14.561 --> 13:18.231
I'm gonna go look
at the couch again.

13:18.264 --> 13:20.266
<i>I didn't know where Tonya was,</i>

13:20.300 --> 13:22.335
<i>but I was praying</i>
<i>she went home.</i>

13:22.369 --> 13:23.536
[BUZZING]

13:23.570 --> 13:25.171
Come on.

13:26.473 --> 13:28.575
What?

13:30.143 --> 13:32.345
Open the door.
I ain't opening nothing.

13:32.379 --> 13:35.081
I'm telling Mama and Daddy
that you said you hate me

13:35.115 --> 13:37.083
and you left me
in the house by myself.

13:37.117 --> 13:39.386
<i>My mother didn't care</i>
<i>what I said to Tonya</i>

13:39.419 --> 13:42.589
<i>just as long as I didn't</i>
<i>leave her someplace by herself.</i>

13:42.622 --> 13:45.925
Didn't I tell you not to leave
your sister here by herself?!

13:45.959 --> 13:48.595
I didn't know she was
gonna sell the house.

13:50.363 --> 13:52.432
[SIGHS]

13:52.465 --> 13:54.434
Open the door!
No!

13:54.467 --> 13:56.936
Why can't you do
what I tell you sometimes?

13:56.970 --> 13:59.472
You said you hate me.
I ain't doing nothing.

13:59.506 --> 14:01.041
That's why I hate you!

14:01.074 --> 14:02.909
Every time I try
to do something,

14:02.942 --> 14:03.977
you always mess it up.

14:04.010 --> 14:05.645
I'm always stuck with you!

14:05.679 --> 14:07.280
I don't feel like your brother,

14:07.313 --> 14:10.250
I feel like
a 13-year-old father.

14:10.283 --> 14:13.653
Dag, man. You're
a 13-year-old father too?

14:13.687 --> 14:15.221
<i>I know he doesn't look 13,</i>

14:15.255 --> 14:16.956
<i>but having kids</i>
<i>will do that to you.</i>

14:16.990 --> 14:19.526
She's not my daughter.

14:19.559 --> 14:21.294
She's my sister.

14:28.134 --> 14:30.170
I can work you out
a great deal on the TV,

14:30.203 --> 14:31.638
the sofa, dining room set.

14:31.671 --> 14:33.473
Get it today,
I'll save you some money.

14:33.506 --> 14:36.142
If I don't get it at all,
I'll save more. Let's go.

14:36.176 --> 14:38.144
Now, wait a minute, Julius.

14:38.178 --> 14:42.949
You work, I work--
Well, sometimes.

14:42.982 --> 14:46.119
I'm just saying,
you don't have to be so ch...

14:48.221 --> 14:50.223
You think I want to be cheap?

14:50.256 --> 14:52.225
I'd love to buy
everything in the store,

14:52.258 --> 14:54.661
but I don't have it
like that, Rochelle.

14:54.694 --> 14:56.329
I don't.

14:56.363 --> 14:58.365
<i>My father wasn't bald</i>
<i>when he got married,</i>

14:58.398 --> 15:01.568
<i>but one hair fell out</i>
<i>for every bill he got.</i>

15:01.601 --> 15:06.106
You know what, forget it, baby.

15:07.340 --> 15:09.142
Huh?

15:09.175 --> 15:12.245
If I buy this stuff, that means
you'll have to work even harder,

15:12.278 --> 15:14.247
which means
you'll be home even less.

15:14.280 --> 15:16.149
And when you do get home,
I'll be mad,

15:16.182 --> 15:18.385
you'll get tired of it,
we'll end up in a divorce,

15:18.418 --> 15:21.221
and I'll end up with some
old-ass furniture and no man.

15:21.254 --> 15:23.690
And if you<i>think</i>you leaving me
for a white woman,

15:23.723 --> 15:25.959
you got another thing coming.

15:27.327 --> 15:29.996
<i>I know you think</i>
<i>she's doing this out of love,</i>

15:30.030 --> 15:32.399
<i>but watch this.</i>

15:32.432 --> 15:34.434
What?

15:34.467 --> 15:36.236
Hold on a minute.

15:42.542 --> 15:44.310
How much for this one?

15:52.452 --> 15:53.787
Can we get that one?

15:53.820 --> 15:56.189
It's just more state-of-the-art.

15:56.222 --> 15:58.324
It has the buttons
and knobs that...

15:58.358 --> 16:01.394
I love you. We're getting
that one right there.

16:01.428 --> 16:03.329
Okay.
On sale.

16:05.432 --> 16:07.467
Were you able to get
the clothes done?

16:07.500 --> 16:11.137
We have a little problem.
Oh!

16:11.171 --> 16:14.441
I told you not to put the
coloreds in with the whites.

16:14.474 --> 16:16.176
Mama's gonna kill me.

16:17.610 --> 16:19.746
Hold on, I think
I can fix this.

16:21.848 --> 16:25.418
Excuse me, miss.
Yes?

16:25.452 --> 16:27.387
My brother put coloreds
in with the whites.

16:27.420 --> 16:29.589
Now everything's pink.
Could you help us

16:29.622 --> 16:31.791
get the clothes white again
or my mother's gonna kill him?

16:31.825 --> 16:34.794
Aw, I'll be happy to.
Thank you.

16:37.364 --> 16:41.234
How'd you do that?
I don't know.

16:41.267 --> 16:43.470
<i>When Drew turned 18,</i>
<i>that woman looked him up.</i>

16:43.503 --> 16:47.540
<i>Not to be her boyfriend, she</i>
<i>just loved doing his laundry.</i>

16:54.647 --> 16:56.282
Wow!

16:56.316 --> 16:59.319
See, whiter than they were
when you brought them in.

16:59.352 --> 17:00.153
Hey, thanks.

17:00.186 --> 17:02.389
You want me to teach you
a kill move?

17:02.422 --> 17:04.224
No, that's okay.

17:04.257 --> 17:07.694
When you turn 18,
you call me, okay?

17:07.727 --> 17:09.095
Okay.

17:09.129 --> 17:11.431
Let's go get these
in the dryers.

17:17.837 --> 17:20.707
<i>Even though my mother was</i>
<i>gonna kill me about Tonya,</i>

17:20.740 --> 17:24.077
<i>at least she had clean clothes</i>
<i>to bury me in.</i>

17:26.212 --> 17:28.415
Hey, boys.
I have something to tell you!

17:28.448 --> 17:31.117
Wait, wait, your dad's got
something to show you. Come on.

17:31.151 --> 17:33.186
A new TV!
Yeah!

17:33.219 --> 17:34.888
Yeah!
TONYA: Oh!

17:34.921 --> 17:36.456
<i>There's something about knowing</i>

17:36.489 --> 17:38.358
<i>you have an ass whipping</i>
<i>coming up</i>

17:38.391 --> 17:40.560
<i>that overshadows</i>
<i>a brand-new TV.</i>

17:40.593 --> 17:43.496
Heh, so, what'd you
want to tell me, Tonya?

17:47.667 --> 17:50.470
I, uh... I had fun
at the laundromat.

17:50.503 --> 17:52.439
JULIUS: That's nice.
ROCHELLE: Good.

17:52.472 --> 17:55.141
What about you, Chris?
What did you have to say?

17:55.175 --> 17:56.443
CHRIS:
Uh...

17:57.577 --> 18:00.714
Can I still watch<i>Rocky?</i>
Sure.

18:00.747 --> 18:02.716
How'd you get the money
for a TV like this?

18:02.749 --> 18:05.385
Oh, your daddy got it on credit.

18:05.418 --> 18:07.587
KIDS: Credit?!
Yeah.

18:07.620 --> 18:09.255
Since you
got this on credit,

18:09.289 --> 18:11.257
think you could get
me some new nunchucks?

18:11.291 --> 18:12.525
You know, a kimono?
No, look.

18:12.559 --> 18:14.361
We're not getting
no more on credit

18:14.394 --> 18:16.162
till this is paid off.
Can we watch<i>Three's Company?</i>

18:16.196 --> 18:18.164
No!
Yes!

18:18.198 --> 18:20.166
I need to watch basketball!
Yes, she can.

18:20.200 --> 18:21.568
It's only a half-hour.

18:21.601 --> 18:23.336
<i>Tonya sure was lucky</i>
<i>she didn't tell,</i>

18:23.370 --> 18:24.738
<i>'cause I was two seconds away</i>

18:24.771 --> 18:27.407
<i>from hitting her</i>
<i>with the monkey claw.</i>

18:30.610 --> 18:33.380
I thought you were
gonna tell on me.

18:33.413 --> 18:34.881
I was.

18:34.914 --> 18:37.250
But I decided not to.

18:39.352 --> 18:41.554
Do you hate me, for real?

18:46.893 --> 18:49.195
No, I don't really hate you.

18:49.229 --> 18:52.165
It's just that you get
on my nerves sometimes.

18:53.633 --> 18:55.268
I'm sorry.

18:57.937 --> 19:00.907
So did you get
your clothes clean?

19:00.940 --> 19:02.876
Yeah.

19:02.909 --> 19:04.611
That's good.

19:05.712 --> 19:07.747
Just because
I said "I'm sorry,"

19:07.781 --> 19:10.316
doesn't mean I'm not gonna
get you in trouble again.

19:10.350 --> 19:14.454
And if I say "I hate you,"
you better not get mad.

19:20.627 --> 19:22.228
[SIGHS]

19:23.830 --> 19:26.900
CHRIS:
Ooh, good jab.

19:26.933 --> 19:29.669
Oh!
JULIUS: Oh!

19:31.538 --> 19:33.773
Drew.

19:33.807 --> 19:35.675
<i>Before I went to sleep</i>
<i>that night,</i>

19:35.709 --> 19:38.678
<i>I had to watch</i>
<i>my favorite movie,</i>Rocky.

19:38.712 --> 19:42.248
<i>It was the perfect way</i>
<i>to end the day.</i>

19:46.686 --> 19:48.922
Chris!

19:48.955 --> 19:50.557
<i>Almost perfect.</i>

19:50.590 --> 19:54.561
<i>* Everybody hates Chris. </i>

19:56.930 --> 19:59.532
[***]

19:59.566 --> 20:02.502
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>
